    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s and Szemer\\'{e}di, who proved that for every $A$\\[F(A,X,3) \\ll X^{1/3}\\log X,\\]and there is an $A$ such that\\[F(A,X,3) \\gg X^{1/3}\\log X\\]for infinitely many $X$. There may be a sequence for which this holds for every $X$."
