    "ambiguity_status": "clear",
    "intended": "Let $A=\\{a_1<a_2<\\cdots\\}\\subseteq \\mathbb{N}$ and let $F(A,X,k)$ count the number of $i$ such that\\[[a_i,a_{i+1},\\ldots,a_{i+k-1}] < X,\\]where the left-hand side is the least common multiple. Is it true that, for every $\\epsilon >0$, there exists some $k$ such that\\[F(A,X,k)<X^\\epsilon?\\]",
